Traffic law enforcement officers are currently diverting traffic onto the Numbi road due to a part of the road collapsing at Klipkopjie Dam. This is due to the heavy rainfall that the Lowveld has been experiencing since yesterday, February 9. ALSO READ: Mpumalanga Disaster Management urges all to be cautious in ongoing rains The collapsed section now extends over 50% of the road surface. Motorists travelling from White River to Hazyview are advised to do so via the R538 (the Numbi road).